    • Constructor Detail

      • SynthesizePN

        SynthesizePN(RegionUtility utility,
             PNProperties properties,
             boolean onlyEventSeparation,
             java.lang.String stateMappingExtension,
             boolean quickFail)
      throws MissingLocationException
        Synthesize a Petri Net which generates the given transition system.
        Parameters:
        utility - An instance of RegionUtility for the requested transition system.
        properties - Properties that the synthesized Petri net should satisfy.
        onlyEventSeparation - Should state separation be ignored? This means that two different states might get the same marking.
        stateMappingExtension - An extension key that will be used to map States. All states in the input transition system must have this extension and it must refer to a State object.
        quickFail - If true, stop the calculation as soon as it is known that it won't be successful. If false, try to solve all separation problems. Only if true will the list of failed problems be fully filled.
        Throws:
        MissingLocationException - if the transition system for the utility has locations for only some events

      • calculateRequiredRegionsAndProblems

        private static void calculateRequiredRegionsAndProblems(RegionUtility utility,
                                                        java.util.Set<java.util.Set<Region>> separationProblems,
                                                        java.util.Set<Region> requiredRegions,
                                                        java.util.Set<Region> remainingRegions,
                                                        boolean onlyEventSeparation)
        Calculate definitely required regions and for each remaining separation problem all regions which solve this problem.
        Parameters:
        utility - The region utility on which this function should work.
        separationProblems - For each still unsolved separation problem, the set of all regions that solve it is calculated and added to this argument.
        requiredRegions - Regions which are definitely required will be added to this set.
        remainingRegions - Regions to choose from and if they are definitely required to move to requiredRegions.
        onlyEventSeparation - Should state separation be ignored?

        Parameters:

        requiredRegions - Set of regions to minimize. Redundant regions will be removed.
        onlyEventSeparation - Should state separation be ignored?

      • isGeneralizedTNet

        public static boolean isGeneralizedTNet(PetriNet pn)
        Check if the PetriNet is a generalized T-Net. In a T-Net, every place has a preset and postset with at most one entry. In a generalized T-Net, arc weights are allowed.
        Parameters:
        pn - The Petri net to check
        Returns:
        true if the pn is a generalized T-Net.

      • isGeneralizedMarkedGraph

        Parameters:

        Returns:
